==English==
===Etymology===
From late Latin [[#Latin|metropolis]], from [[Ancient Greek]] '''[[μητρόπολις]]''' (''metropolis'') ‘mother city’, from '''[[μήτηρ]]''' (''meter'') ‘mother’ + '''[[πόλις]]''' (''polis'') ‘city’.

===Noun===
{{en-noun|'''[[metropolises]]''' or '''[[metropoli]]'''}}

# The [[see]] of a metropolitan [[bishop]].
# The chief [[city]] of a colony, especially in ancient Greece.
# Any large, busy city, especially as the main city in an area or country or as distinguished from surrounding rural areas.

